ene encoding glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase: the last homeless enzyme of aromatic amino acids biosynthesis\n\n[Matthieu Graindorge](/?term=Graindorge+M&cauthor_id=20883697)¬Ý [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"Universit√© Grenoble 1, Grenoble, France.\") ,¬Ý[C√©cile Giustini](/?term=Giustini+C&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Anne Claire Jacomin](/?term=Jacomin+AC&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Alexandra Kraut](/?term=Kraut+A&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Gilles Curien](/?term=Curien+G&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Michel Matringe](/?term=Matringe+M&cauthor_id=20883697)\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Universit√© Grenoble 1, Grenoble, France.\n\n-   PMID: **20883697**\n-   DOI: [10.1016/j.febslet.2010.09.037](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.febslet.2010.09.037)\n\nFree article\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# Identification of a plant gene encoding glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase: the last homeless enzyme of aromatic amino acids biosynthesis\n\nMatthieu Graindorge¬Ýet al. FEBS Lett. 2010.\n\nFree article\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nFEBS Lett\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22FEBS+Lett%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22FEBS+Lett%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2010 Oct 22;584(20):4357-60.\n\ndoi: 10.1016/j.febslet.2010.09.037. Epub 2010 Sep 29.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Matthieu Graindorge](/?term=Graindorge+M&cauthor_id=20883697)¬Ý [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Universit√© Grenoble 1, Grenoble, France.\") ,¬Ý[C√©cile Giustini](/?term=Giustini+C&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Anne Claire Jacomin](/?term=Jacomin+AC&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Alexandra Kraut](/?term=Kraut+A&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Gilles Curien](/?term=Curien+G&cauthor_id=20883697),¬Ý[Michel Matringe](/?term=Matringe+M&cauthor_id=20883697)\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Universit√© Grenoble 1, Grenoble, France.\n\n-   PMID: **20883697**\n-   DOI: [10.1016/j.febslet.2010.09.037](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.febslet.2010.09.037)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nIn all organisms synthesising phenylalanine and/or tyrosine via arogenate, a prephenate aminotransferase is required for the transamination of prephenate into arogenate. The identity of the gene encoding this enzyme in the organisms where this activity occurs is still unknown. Glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase (PAT) is thus the last homeless enzyme in the aromatic amino acids pathway. We report on the purification, mass spectrometry identification and biochemical characterization of Arabidopsis thaliana prephenate aminotransferase. Our data revealed that this activity is housed by the prokaryotic-type plastidic aspartate aminotransferase (At2g22250). This represents the first identification of a gene encoding PAT.\n\nCopyright ¬© 2010 Federation of European Biochemical Societies. Published by Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Amino Acids, Aromatic / metabolism\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Amino+Acids%2C+Aromatic%2Fmetabolism%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Amino+Acids%2C+Aromatic)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Arabidopsis / cytology\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Arabidopsis%2Fcytology%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Arabidopsis)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Arabidopsis / enzymology\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Arabidopsis%2Fenzymology%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Arabidopsis)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Arabidopsis / genetics